{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d5d0d01c-179b-47dc-a8c5-01f992b7dd5b","content":"There's no pipeline file in the current directory, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Replace `VSTest@3` with `DotNetCoreCLI@2` (or a plain `dotnet test` script):**\n\n```yaml\n# Before (VSTest runner)\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testAssemblies: '**/*Tests.dll'\n    runSettingsFile: test.runsettings\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n\n# After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform via dotnet test)\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**2. Enable Microsoft.Testing.Platform** in each test project:\n\n```xml\n<!-- In your test .csproj -->\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nEnsure you're on **MSTest 3.x+** NuGet packages.\n\n**3. Publish results & coverage** (TRX + code coverage):\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\nIf you use the `.coverage` binary format instead of Cobertura, add a `.runsettings` file to switch:\n\n```xml\n<RunSettings>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <Format>Cobertura</Format>\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nThen pass `--settings test.runsettings` in the `arguments`.\n\n### Summary of changes\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Runner | `VSTest@3` task | `dotnet test` / `DotNetCoreCLI@2` |\n| TRX output | Built-in | `--logger \"trx\"` |\n| Coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled: true` | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` + runsettings |\n| Publish results | Automatic | `PublishTestResults@2` (add `condition: always()`) |\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific pipeline file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3b9f90d0-b413-4da2-9795-64402c5575d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no pipeline files in the repository. The user is asking a general question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":787,"requestId":"2867:418E1:15EC5B5:17519A2:6A045FD0"},"id":"a530b0a4-8f23-424e-a4c7-fea9d114d648","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:26:25.309Z","parentId":"d27b2041-da60-4aba-9d06-9477a4da17be"}
